3 in accordance with and subject to IC 5-14-1.5. All records of the
4 task force shall be subject to the requirements of IC 5-14-3.
5 Sec. 6. The task force shall study the following:
6 (1) Recodification of IC 29-3 (guardianships and protective
7 proceedings) in a style that is clear, concise, and easy to
8 interpret and apply.
9 (2) Improvements to the guardianship code that:
10 (A) increase procedural protections for minors and adults
11 who are subject to a guardianship procedure, including
12 enforcement mechanisms concerning supported decision
13 making;
14 (B) clearly distinguish between adult and minor
15 guardianships; and
16 (C) update terminology, including the use of people first
17 and person centered language.
18 Sec. 7. The task force shall make recommendations based upon
19 the study conducted under section 6 of this chapter.
20 Sec. 8. (a) The task force may, not later than November 1, 2026,
21 prepare a status report describing the progress made under section
22 6 of this chapter. The status report may also contain proposed
23 legislation based on recommendations made under this chapter.
24 (b) If the report submitted under subsection (a), does not
25 contain proposed legislation, the task force shall, not later than
26 November 1, 2027, submit a report of proposed legislation based on
27 recommendations made under this chapter.
28 (c) A report issued under this section must be submitted:
29 (1) in an electronic format under IC 5-14-6 to the executive
30 director of the legislative services agency for distribution to
31 the members of the general assembly; and
32 (2) to the governor.
33 Sec. 9. The legislative services agency shall provide staff support
34 to the task force.
