7 SECTION 2. IC 29-3-3-1 IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
8 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) Any person indebted to a
9 minor or having possession of property belonging to a minor in an
10 amount not exceeding ten twenty-five thousand dollars ($10,000)
11 ($25,000) may pay the debt or deliver the property without the
12 appointment of a guardian, giving of bond, or other order of court
13 directly to:
14 (1) any person having the care and custody of the minor with
15 whom the minor resides; or
16 (2) a custodian for the benefit of the minor under IC 30-2-8.5.
17 (b) Persons receiving property for a minor under this section are
18 obligated to apply the property to the support, use, and benefit of the
19 minor.
20 (c) This section does not apply if the person paying or delivering the
21 property knows that a guardian has been appointed for the minor or that
22 proceedings for appointment of a guardian for the minor are pending.
23 (d) A person who pays or delivers property in accordance with this
24 section in good faith is not responsible for the proper application of that
25 property.
