12 the individual if the individual has specifically granted the authority of
13 the health care representative to supersede the authority of the attorney
14 in fact in the executed power of attorney.
15 (e) Notwithstanding any other law, a document granting health care
16 powers to an attorney in fact for health care may not be executed under
17 this chapter after December 31, 2022. However, if a power of attorney
18 that is executed after December 31, 2022, is written to grant both:
19 (1) health care powers; and
20 (2) nonhealth care powers under this chapter;
21 to an attorney in fact, the health care powers are void, but all other
22 powers granted by the power of attorney will remain effective and
23 enforceable under this article.
24 SECTION 10. IC 32-17-8-3.5, AS ADDED BY P.L.61-2024,
25 SECTION 3, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
26 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3.5. When the an initial power of appointment in
27 a legacy trust is exercised to create a second subsequent power of
28 appointment or nonvested property interest, the subsequent power
29 of appointment or a nonvested property interest or the second power
30 of appointment created through the exercise of the initial power of
31 appointment is considered to have been created at the time of the
32 irrevocable exercise creation of the initial power of appointment,
33 unless:
34 (1) the instrument exercising creating the initial power of
35 appointment; or
36 (2) the instrument exercising the initial power of
37 appointment;
38 explicitly provides that the second subsequent power of appointment
39 was is considered to have been created at the time of the creation
40 irrevocable exercise of the initial power of appointment.
